The Sporting Schools Program provides funding for schools to partner with local sports clubs and deliver quality sport programs to primary school students.

## Overview

This is an excellent pathway for clubs to grow junior membership while receiving funding to deliver coaching and programs. Schools receive the funding and partner with your club to deliver sessions.

## How It Works

1. Your club registers as a Sporting Schools delivery partner
2. Local schools apply for funding through the program
3. Schools select your club as their delivery partner
4. Your club delivers sport sessions at the school
5. Your club invoices the school for the agreed amount

## Benefits for Clubs

- Direct pathway to junior membership growth
- Paid coaching opportunities for your volunteers
- Increased community visibility
- Relationship building with local schools

## Getting Started

1. Visit the Sporting Schools website and register your club
2. Ensure your coaches have current Working With Children Checks
3. Develop a simple program outline suitable for primary school students
4. Reach out to local schools to introduce your club

